<div class="tldr-box">
  <h3>TL;DR, Refrens for Indian freelancers</h3>
  <p>The default invoicing OS for Indian freelancers and small services businesses. Free tier is generous; paid tiers add GST/TDS automation and team features. Strong AI for quotations, follow-up emails, and client research. UPI works, GST invoice native, TDS handled. If you have ever struggled with quoting/invoicing/collecting from Indian clients, this is the fix.</p>
  <a href="https://www.refrens.com" class="cta-button">Try Refrens (free)</a>
</div>

<p>The hardest part of Indian freelance work is rarely the work itself. It is the surrounding business: quoting properly, invoicing in the correct GST format, collecting payment from clients who delay by weeks, handling the TDS deduction your client made, and looking professional through it all.</p>

<p>Refrens is the Indian-built freelancer business OS that solves the bulk of this with practical workflow plus genuine AI in a few key places. This is the honest review for solo freelancers, small agencies, consultants, and services businesses in 2026.</p>

<h2>What Refrens actually does</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Quotations and proposals</strong>, Templates plus AI-assisted drafting. Send a professional quote in 5 minutes.</li>
  <li><strong>GST-compliant invoicing</strong>, Auto-formats with your GSTIN, client GSTIN, HSN/SAC codes, CGST/SGST/IGST split, place of supply, reverse charge. The boring stuff that gets you a 50% short-paid invoice when missing.</li>
  <li><strong>Payment links</strong>, UPI plus Indian cards plus international cards. The link goes in your invoice email; your client pays in 30 seconds.</li>
  <li><strong>Recurring invoices</strong>, Set once, sent monthly to retainer clients.</li>
  <li><strong>Expense and TDS tracking</strong>, Match TDS deducted by clients against Form 26AS at year-end. This single feature saves hours.</li>
  <li><strong>Client and lead CRM</strong>, Tag clients, follow up on overdue invoices, see who has paid and who hasn't at a glance.</li>
  <li><strong>AI features</strong>, Quotation drafting from a brief, follow-up email drafting, client research, pricing suggestions.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Where Refrens beats global alternatives for Indians</h2>

<h3>GST invoicing done right</h3>
<p>Most global tools (FreshBooks, Wave, Stripe Invoicing) do not understand Indian GST. They miss HSN codes, mis-handle reverse charge, do not split CGST/SGST/IGST based on place of supply, and produce invoices Indian clients reject. Refrens does this natively.</p>

<h3>Payment collection that actually works for Indian clients</h3>
<p>If your client is Indian, they want to pay via UPI. Generating a payment link that accepts UPI plus cards plus net banking is the single biggest collection accelerator. Refrens does this out of the box.</p>

<h3>TDS reconciliation</h3>
<p>Indian clients deduct 10% TDS on professional fees under Section 194J. At year-end you reconcile this against Form 26AS to claim the credit. Refrens tracks every TDS deducted across your invoices and produces the reconciliation. This is a freelancer-specific Indian workflow no global tool handles.</p>

<h3>Pricing in INR</h3>
<p>The Refrens free tier is genuinely free. Paid tiers are priced in INR for Indian freelancer economics, not US enterprise budgets. UPI subscription works.</p>

<h2>Where the AI in Refrens actually helps</h2>

<h3>AI quotation drafting</h3>
<p>Paste a client brief in 2 lines, get a structured quotation with deliverables, timeline, payment terms, and your branded template. Edit in 30 seconds rather than writing from scratch. For freelancers sending 5+ quotes a week this compounds.</p>

<h3>Follow-up email drafting</h3>
<p>The most awkward part of freelancing is chasing payment. Refrens drafts a context-aware follow-up email (third reminder, payment 45 days overdue, polite but firm). You edit and send.</p>

<h3>Client research and proposal AI</h3>
<p>Newer feature. Paste a client company name, get a brief on their business, recent news, likely budget range, and a suggested proposal angle. Useful for preparing pitches to prospects you do not know well.</p>

<h3>Auto-categorisation</h3>
<p>For expenses and invoices, AI suggests categories based on description, speeding up bookkeeping.</p>

<h2>Best Indian use cases</h2>

<h3>Solo Indian freelancers (writers, designers, developers, consultants)</h3>
<p>The sweet spot. Free tier handles most of the workflow. Quotations, invoices, UPI collection, follow-ups, TDS reconciliation at year-end. The hour-per-week saved on admin pays back hundredfold in client-billable hours.</p>

<h3>Small Indian agencies (2-10 people)</h3>
<p>Paid tier with team features for the same workflow at scale. Multi-user, role-based access, client portal, project-level billing.</p>

<h3>Consultants and coaches</h3>
<p>Recurring invoicing for retainer clients, advance payment workflow, client onboarding documents. Refrens handles this cleanly.</p>

<h3>Indian D2C ops handling B2B invoicing</h3>
<p>If you sell wholesale to retailers, the GST-correct invoicing and payment-link workflow is the same use case.</p>

<h2>Where Refrens is not the right tool</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>You need full double-entry accounting</strong>, Refrens is invoicing-first, not accounting-first. Use Zoho Books or Tally if you need P&amp;L, balance sheet, audit-ready books.</li>
  <li><strong>Your business is product-heavy with inventory</strong>, Inventory management is not Refrens' strength.</li>
  <li><strong>You serve only US/EU clients in USD</strong>, Global-focused tools (Stripe, Wise) may fit better.</li>
  <li><strong>You need detailed time-tracking integrated with invoicing</strong>, Pair with Toggl or Clockify; Refrens has basic time tracking but specialist tools are deeper.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Indian alternatives</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Zoho Invoice / Zoho Books</strong>, More accounting-heavy, broader product line, slightly slower to set up for pure freelancer use.</li>
  <li><strong>Razorpay Invoice</strong>, Excellent Indian payment story, fewer freelancer-specific workflow features.</li>
  <li><strong>Vyapar</strong>, Strong for offline-first small business invoicing, less AI.</li>
  <li><strong>FreshBooks, QuickBooks, Wave</strong>, Global tools, weaker GST/TDS handling for Indian freelancers.</li>
</ul>

